    "themes": ["God\'92s power", "hope", "trust"],\
    "summary": "A heartfelt song that builds confidence in God\'92s unlimited ability. It encourages the church that no matter how impossible a situation seems, God is more than able to turn it around. By reflecting on God\'92s past faithfulness, it stirs hope that He can do it again, leading the congregation into deeper trust and expectation.",\
    "theology": "\'93More Than Able\'94 proclaims Ephesians 3:20 \'96 that God can do exceedingly above all we ask or imagine. Its theology elevates God\'92s omnipotence and goodness; where we see limits, God sees opportunity for His glory. The lyrics remind us that creation itself testifies of His power (Jeremiah 32:17), and that our small faith is met by His great faithfulness (Matthew 17:20). It also emphasizes surrender, implying that when we step aside (\'93who am I to deny what the Lord can do?\'94), we acknowledge God\'92s sovereignty. In essence, the song teaches that our hope is secure not in our own strength or plans, but in the God for whom nothing is impossible (Luke 1:37).",\
    "scripture_references": ["Ephesians 3:20", "Jeremiah 32:17", "Luke 1:37"],\
    "practical_worship_leadership": "Lead this song when your community needs encouragement to trust God for big things \'96 whether it\'92s healing, provision, or breakthrough. Start gently, perhaps even sharing a quick testimony of something God has done in your church to set the tone. As the song progresses and swells, invite the congregation to bring their personal \'93impossible\'94 situations to mind and sing these truths over them. Musically, take advantage of dynamic contrasts: drop to a whisper on \'93who am I to deny\'85\'94 then rise strong into the chorus to symbolize faith rising. This song could naturally flow into a time of prayer for needs or silence for reflection on God\'92s capability before concluding with a final refrain of confident praise.",\
    "seo_title": "More Than Able \'96 Elevation Worship Song",\
    "meta_description": "\'93More Than Able\'94 by Elevation Worship is an inspiring song about God\'92s unlimited power and our trust in Him. Learn about its biblical affirmation that nothing is impossible for God, and find practical insights for leading your congregation in this hope-filled anthem."\
