    "summary": "A declarative worship song often sung around baptisms, celebrating the believer\'92s death to sin and resurrection to new life in Christ. Its lyrics reaffirm our decision to follow Jesus, stating that the old self has been buried and we stand forgiven and free because of His grace.",\
    "theology": "\'93Beneath The Waters\'94 is rooted in the imagery of baptism as described in Romans 6:3-4 \'96 being buried with Christ and raised to walk in newness of life. The song proclaims key salvation truths: that by Christ\'92s sacrifice our sin is washed away and we are made alive in Him (Colossians 2:12-14). It carries a strong theme of covenant, echoing Galatians 2:20 (\'93I have been crucified with Christ and I no longer live, but Christ lives in me\'94). Each phrase like \'93I stand a new creation\'94 and \'93sin has no hold on me\'94 is a theological assertion of our identity in Christ and the complete work of atonement. The bridge (\'93I rise as You are risen\'94) emphasizes that the power which raised Jesus now empowers us to live victoriously (Ephesians 1:19-20).",\
    "scripture_references": ["Romans 6:3-4", "Galatians 2:20", "Colossians 2:12-14"],\
    "practical_worship_leadership": "This song is a natural choice for baptism services or any time you want to reaffirm the basics of the gospel in song. If you are using it during baptisms, coordinate so that the most declarative parts (like the bridge or final chorus) coincide with the moment someone comes up out of the water \'96 it can be very powerful. Lead with confident joy; even though it starts gently, it\'92s a song of triumph. Encourage those who have been believers a long time to sing it as a renewal of their commitment. Instrumentally, build momentum gradually and let the congregation\'92s voices ring on \'93I will rise\'94 \'96 even drop out the band on a repeat of that line to let the church declare it together. Ending with a strong cadence can underscore the finality of \'93no turning back\'94 in our decision to follow Christ.",\
    "seo_title": "Beneath The Waters (I Will Rise) \'96 Hillsong Worship",\
    "meta_description": "\'93Beneath The Waters (I Will Rise)\'94 by Hillsong Worship is a powerful song of baptism and new life in Christ. Delve into its biblical references to dying and rising with Jesus, its declarations of faith and forgiveness, and tips for leading it effectively \'96 especially in baptismal services."\
