    "themes": ["God\'92s presence", "comfort", "faithfulness"],\
    "summary": "A comforting worship ballad that speaks directly into fear and loneliness, assuring the believer that God goes before us and won\'92t leave us. Its heartfelt lyrics help the congregation to personally affirm God\'92s promise, \'93You will never leave me,\'94 and to rest in His faithful presence in every trial.",\
    "theology": "\'93I Am Not Alone\'94 is built on God\'92s promises of companionship and protection (Isaiah 43:2). Theologically, it underscores God\'92s immanence \'96 He is with His people through every circumstance (Psalm 23:4). The song acknowledges that believers will walk through deep waters and fires, yet boldly claims the truth of Deuteronomy 31:8 that the Lord goes before us and will not forsake us. By repeating \'93You amaze me, redeem me, You call me as Your own,\'94 it highlights our identity as God\'92s children and His active work to rescue and claim us. In essence, the song is a musical reminder of Jesus\'92 words, \'93I am with you always\'94 (Matthew 28:20), assuring us that we never fight our battles alone.",\
    "scripture_references": ["Deuteronomy 31:8", "Isaiah 43:2", "Psalm 23:4"],\
    "practical_worship_leadership": "Introduce this song in services focused on encouragement, mental health, or when many seem to be walking through hardship. It\'92s a gentle, slow-tempo piece, so create a reflective environment \'96 dimmer lighting, perhaps encourage people to close their eyes or lift their hands in a receiving posture. Because its lyrics are almost like prayer, you might softly speak a line like \'93Hear God saying to you: you\'92re not alone\'94 before singing. Musically, maintain a warm, steady accompaniment (pad, strings, or piano) that supports without overpowering. As you lead the bridge (\'93You amaze me\'85You call me as Your own\'94), consider stepping back from the mic slightly to let the congregation hear themselves declaring those powerful words. End the song softly, maybe repeating \'93I am not alone\'94 and allowing a brief silence afterwards for people to sense God\'92s comforting presence.",\
    "seo_title": "I Am Not Alone \'96 Kari Jobe Worship Song",\
    "meta_description": "\'93I Am Not Alone\'94 by Kari Jobe is a comforting worship song about God\'92s unfailing presence in our trials. Discover the biblical promises of God\'92s nearness it proclaims and get practical advice on leading this song to minister peace and hope to your congregation."\
