    "themes": ["seeking God", "repentance", "first love"],\
    "summary": "A heartfelt, stripped-down song of repentance and desire that centers on returning to the \'93heart of worship.\'94 In \'93Nothing Else,\'94 the church sings of laying aside agendas and achievements, coming back to Jesus with the simple longing to be in His presence \'96 because nothing else will satisfy.",\
    "theology": "\'93Nothing Else\'94 echoes the cry of Psalm 27:4 \'96 that the one thing we seek is God Himself. Theologically, it\'92s a song of reorientation: acknowledging how easily we can get distracted even in spiritual activity, it voices repentance reminiscent of Revelation 2:4-5 (returning to our first love). The lyrics confess that even blessings and miracles are secondary to simply knowing Jesus. It affirms God as the ultimate reward (Genesis 15:1) and that in His presence is our fulfillment. By declaring \'93I just want You,\'94 the song aligns with Philippians 3:8, counting all things loss compared to the surpassing worth of Christ. In essence, it\'92s about pure devotion \'96 valuing the Giver far above His gifts.",\
    "scripture_references": ["Psalm 27:4", "Philippians 3:8", "Revelation 2:4-5"],\
    "practical_worship_leadership": "This song often shines in intimate worship settings or after a convicting message where response is needed. Consider leading it with minimal instrumentation (just piano or guitar) to maintain its raw, prayerful tone. Encourage authenticity \'96 perhaps invite the congregation to take a posture of humility (like kneeling or hands open) as they sing. There are moments of silence in the original recording; don\'92t be afraid of those \'96 they allow personal reflection. You might whisper a short prayer between verses (\'93Lord, we\'92re sorry when we\'92ve come with our own agenda\'85\'94). Use \'93Nothing Else\'94 to usher in times of altar ministry or lingering prayer, as it naturally creates a space where hearts are tender and focused solely on seeking Jesus.",\
    "seo_title": "Nothing Else \'96 Cody Carnes Worship Song",\
    "meta_description": "\'93Nothing Else\'94 by Cody Carnes is an intimate worship song about seeking Jesus above all else and returning to our first love. Learn about its foundation in Scripture, its theme of repentance and pure devotion, and effective ways to lead this song in a worship service."\
