    "themes": ["praise", "joy", "God\'92s glory"],\
    "summary": "A joyful, call-and-response gospel anthem that unites the congregation in simple, exuberant praise. Repeating the phrase \'93every praise is to our God,\'94 it leaves no doubt that all worship \'96 in song, in shout, in dance \'96 belongs to Him alone. It\'92s an infectious celebration of God\'92s goodness and deliverance.",\
    "theology": "The theology of \'93Every Praise\'94 is straightforward and exuberant: God alone is worthy of all our praise (Psalm 150:6). It emphasizes unity in worship \'96 the entire song is an invitation for everyone to participate (\'93sing hallelujah to our God\'94). The bridge reinforces God\'92s saving nature by declaring Him \'93Savior, Healer, Deliverer,\'94 echoing biblical truths of God\'92s character (Isaiah 43:11, Exodus 15:26, Psalm 40:17). By repeating these titles three times (a common gospel music technique), it subtly mirrors the triplet praise seen in \'93holy, holy, holy,\'94 giving a fullness to the declaration. Overall, the song teaches that praising God is not just an individual act but a corporate one, and that in doing so we acknowledge His power to save and set free.",\
    "scripture_references": ["Psalm 150:6", "Isaiah 43:11", "Jude 1:25"],\
    "practical_worship_leadership": "This song is high-energy and participatory \'96 perfect as an opener or closing praise. Encourage clapping from the start, and don\'92t hesitate to physically move and smile as you lead; your enthusiasm will be contagious. Because it\'92s repetitive (in a good way), you can split parts of the room for call-and-response or have a choir echo you if available. It\'92s a great opportunity to incorporate multilingual or multicultural elements (e.g., inviting those who speak other languages to shout \'93hallelujah\'94 in their language). Instrumentally, keep the groove tight \'96 a strong bass line and drums are key. End with a big finish, possibly holding out \'93God\'94 while music cuts, to drive home that every praise indeed belongs to Him.",\
